text: 25H-NBOMe (NBOMe-2C-H) is a derivative of the phenethylamine hallucinogen 2C-H, which acts as a highly potent partial agonist for the human 5-HT2A receptor.https://bitnest.netfirms.com/external.php?id=%257DbxUaPRU%2505%255CG%252B%2527%252AFQ%2502%2518%2508U%250ATv ==Legality== ===Sweden=== The Riksdag added 25H-NBOMe to Narcotic Drugs Punishments Act under swedish schedule I ("substances, plant materials and fungi which normally do not have medical use") as of August 1, 2013, published by Medical Products Agency (MPA) in regulation LVFS 2013:15 listed as 25H-NBOMe, and 2-(2,5-dimetoxifenyl)-N-(2-metoxibensyl)etanamin.https://lakemedelsverket.se/upload/lvfs/LVFS_2013-15.pdf ===United Kingdom=== == See also == * 2CBCB-NBOMe (NBOMe-TCB-2) * 2CBFly-NBOMe (NBOMe-2CB-Fly) * 2C-C-NBOMe (NBOMe-2CC) * 25B-NBOMe (NBOMe-2CB) * 25I-NBOMe (NBOMe-2CI) * 25I-NBMD (NBMD-2CI) * 25B-NBOH * 25I-NBOH (NBOH-2CI) == References == Category:25-NB (psychedelics) Category:Designer drugs
